[[File:Osahozuka & Mesahozuka entrance.JPG|thumb|220px|right|{{center|Entrance to Osahozuka and Mesahozuka {{ill|Mausoleum Reference Site|ja|陵墓参考地|1=Mausoleum Reference Site|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mausoleum Reference Site|13=User:Immanuelle/Mausoleum Reference Site|qq=}}s}}]]
'''Osahozuka Kofun''' ({{lang|ja|男狭穂塚古墳}}, Osahozuka Kofun) is a {{ill|kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Kofun|qq=}} located in {{ill|Saito City|ja|西都市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saito City|qq=}}, Miyazaki Prefecture, Japan. It is part of the {{ill|Saitobaru Kofun Cluster|ja|西都原古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saitobaru Kofun Cluster|qq=}}, specifically within the Maruyama Subcluster, and is the largest {{ill|scallop-shaped kofun|ja|帆立貝形古墳|1=Scallop Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/scallop-shaped kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Scallop Kofun|qq=}} in Japan.

While the actual honoree is unknown, the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Household Agency|qq=}} designates this site as the "Osahozuka {{ill|Mausoleum Reference Site|ja|陵墓参考地|1=Mausoleum Reference Site|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mausoleum Reference Site|13=User:Immanuelle/Mausoleum Reference Site|qq=}}" and identifies {{ill|Ninigi-no-Mikoto|ja|瓊瓊杵尊|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ninigi-no-Mikoto|qq=}} as the presumed honoree. It is adjacent to the {{ill|Mesahozuka Kofun|ja|女狭穂塚古墳|1=Mezasahozuka Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mesahozuka Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Mezasahozuka Kofun|qq=}}, Historic Site1 as the "Mesahozuka {{ill|Mausoleum Reference Site|ja|陵墓参考地|1=Mausoleum Reference Site|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mausoleum Reference Site|13=User:Immanuelle/Mausoleum Reference Site|qq=}}," which is believed to honor Ninigi’s consort, {{ill|Konohanasakuya-hime|ja|木花開耶姫|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Konohanasakuya-hime|qq=}}.

== Overview ==
{{Multiple image
| align = right
| direction = vertical
| width = 180
| image1 = [[File:Osahodzuka air.jpg|frameless]]
| caption1 = Aerial view
| image = [[File:Osahozuka & Mesahozuka entrance.JPG|frameless]]
| caption2 = Entrance to the site
}}
Osahozuka Kofun is located in the central part of the {{ill|Saitobaru Plateau|ja|西都原台地|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saitobaru Plateau|qq=}}, on the right bank of the Hitotsuse River. The site is part of the {{ill|Saitobaru Kofun Cluster|ja|西都原古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saitobaru Kofun Cluster|qq=}}, which includes over 320 Kofuns, making it the largest kofun cluster in Kyushu. Together with the adjacent Mesahozuka Kofun, it types the Maruyama Subcluster along with three smaller associated Kofuns ({{ill|Baizuka|ja|陪塚|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Baizuka|qq=}}).<ref>{{Harvnb|Higashi|2017|11=15-28}}</ref>

The tumulus is scallop-shaped, with a relatively short front section oriented towards the south-southeast. The circular mound is built in three tiers, while the front section has two tiers. The area of the tumulus are as follows:
* Total length: A11roximately 176 m
* Circular mound diameter: 132 m
* Circular mound height: 19.1 m

The surrounding moat system includes two concentric moats, which type an incomplete loop around the mound, missing the front section. Excavations have uncovered fragments of {{ill|haniwa|ja|埴輪|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/haniwa|qq=}}. However, the burial chamber has not been investigated.<ref>{{Harvnb|Higashi|2017|11=29-62}}</ref>

The construction of Osahozuka Kofun is estimated to have taken place in the early 5th century during the middle kofun period, coinciding with the construction of Mesahozuka Kofun. These twin kofun represent the peak of power consolidation in the region.<ref>{{Harvnb|Higashi|2017|11=15-28}}</ref>

== burial goods ==
Fragments of {{ill|haniwa|ja|埴輪|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/haniwa|qq=}} have been recovered from Osahozuka Kofun. These include cylindrical haniwa, notable for their thin walls, fine details, and a reddish-brown coloration indicative of kiln firing. The style is distinct from the open-fire-fired haniwa found at Mesahozuka Kofun.<ref>{{Harvnb|Higashi|2017|11=29-62}}</ref>

== Honoree ==
While the precise identity of the buried individual is unknown, the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Household Agency|qq=}} attributes the burial to {{ill|Ninigi-no-Mikoto|ja|瓊瓊杵尊|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ninigi-no-Mikoto|qq=}}, a deity from Japanese mythology. This attribution is based on records from the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Shoki|qq=}}, which mention Ninigi’s tomb as being in "Kawai-yama of Hyuga" but do not specify its exact location.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Encyclopedia of Imperial Mausolea|author=Yoshikawa Kōbunkan|year=2005}}</ref>

== Access ==
* location: Miyazaki Prefecture, Saito City, Miyake
* Access: From {{ill|Miyakoh City Bus Terminal|ja|宮交シティ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyakoh City Bus Terminal|qq=}}, take a Miyazaki Kōtsū bus to "Saitobaru Archaeological Museum." Alternatively, use a taxi from Saito Bus Center.

